I ended up coming up with another solution instead of using masked input. Here&#39;s my logic I implemented in my app:

The regex for blood pressure will be `[0-9]{0,3}/[0-9]{0-3}`. But instead of putting only the `/`, use `[^a-zA-Z0-9]` to prevent any letter and number to be inserted at the `/` position, and for us to change the `.` in decimal field to `/` later.

```
InputFilter filter = new InputFilter() {
	final int maxDigitsBeforeDecimalPoint=3;
	final int maxDigitsAfterDecimalPoint=3;

	@Override
	public CharSequence filter(CharSequence source, int start, int end, Spanned dest, int dstart, int dend) {
		StringBuilder builder = new StringBuilder(dest);
		builder.replace(dstart, dend, source
				.subSequence(start, end).toString());
		if (!builder.toString().matches(
				&quot;(([1-9]{1})([0-9]{0,&quot;+(maxDigitsBeforeDecimalPoint-1)+&quot;})?)?([^a-zA-z0-9][0-9]{0,&quot;+maxDigitsAfterDecimalPoint+&quot;})?&quot;

		)) {
			if(source.length()==0)
				return dest.subSequence(dstart, dend);
			return &quot;&quot;;
		}
		return null;
	}
};
```

Then, create a `TextWatcher` for the `editText` as well. The first if statement is to prevent the `.` being displayed in the `editText`, since the `editText` is set to `android:inputType=&quot;number|numberDecimal&quot;`. For the second and third if statements is to validate 2 digit inputs and 3 digit inputs respectively. You can add on the logic on validating the inputs after the `/` as well :).
```
bloodPressureAm.setFilters(new InputFilter[] {filter});
bloodPressureAm.addTextChangedListener(new TextWatcher() {
	@Override
	public void beforeTextChanged(CharSequence charSequence, int i, int i1, int i2) {}

	@Override
	public void onTextChanged(CharSequence charSequence, int i, int i1, int i2) {}

	@Override
	public void afterTextChanged(Editable editable) {
		if (String.valueOf(bloodPressureAm.getText()).contains(&quot;.&quot;)){
			bloodPressureAm.setText(String.valueOf(bloodPressureAm.getText()).replace(&quot;.&quot;,&quot;/&quot;));
		}
		//Means it&#39;s going to insert 100+
		if (editable.length() == 2 &amp;&amp; !isDeleting){
			if (Integer.parseInt(String.valueOf(bloodPressureAm.getText())) &gt;= 20){
				bloodPressureAm.setText(bloodPressureAm.getText() + &quot;/&quot;);
			}
		}
		if (editable.length() == 3 &amp;&amp; !isDeleting){
			if (!String.valueOf(bloodPressureAm.getText()).contains(&quot;/&quot;)){
				bloodPressureAm.setText(bloodPressureAm.getText() + &quot;/&quot;);
			}
		}
        //Set the cursor to the end of the editText
		bloodPressureAm.setSelection(bloodPressureAm.getText().length());
	}
});
```
Lastly, since we forced the `/` to be inserted after 2 or 3 digits, we are unable to delete it due to the `TextWatcher`. So, to overcome it, create a `onKeyListener` for `editText`.
```
bloodPressureAm.setOnKeyListener((view, i, keyEvent) -&gt; {
	if (i == KeyEvent.KEYCODE_DEL){
		isDeleting = true;
	}else{
		isDeleting = false;
	}
	return false;
});
```

Hope this helps! &gt;:&gt;

